{"word":"ἄσωτος","slug":"ἄσωτος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄσωτος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:σώζω'><el>σώζω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>having no hope of safety, abandoned, profligate</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>perditus</el>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a>, <el>ἄσωτος γένει</el> <i>bringing ruin on</i> the race, <i>fatal</i> to it, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}